OL,5,Clistening
OL,7,FHe told us his son had come out at
OL,8,Funiversity and embraced his identity
OL,9,Fwith pride. A confident, openly gay
OL,10,Fman, his reputation was important to
OL,11,Fhim. He was successful in his career,
OL,12,Fa popular guy committed to social
OL,13,Fissues right up until the end. Unknown
OL,14,Fto his family, Tahir had been seeking
OL,15,Fhelp for an addiction.
OL,17,FTahir went to meet a guy to have sex
OL,18,Fand take drugs - but this time the
OL,19,Fconsequences were devastating. After
OL,20,Fseveral days using the drugs, an
OL,21,Fambulance was called.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/40
